results.description: One of the brightest orange warblers around the Blackburnian stands out in most forests.  Hearing their very high pitched call is always a joy and then usually means a ton of frustration as I try to find a chance to photograph them in lower branches.  They love the canopy of the forest so in the areas I see them that usually means a ton of patience since they rarely come down.  I caught this lovely male perched in a Hemlock branch.
